<subSubSection id="0EA1C2B00FBC80DDFEE36B3E7B8DCB55" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="8FCC0A7EF5760B7E5EA7512BA27AE51F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A246EFB395B7E562568947464342B4C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Rhizomatous perennial with a stout woody base; stems decumbent to at least 1 m, herbaceous, glabrous. Leaves shortly petiolate, 8-18 
<normalizedToken id="36367276CE9AC9F5F20B439BA8C2B1E3" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-4 cm, lanceolate or oblong-lanceolate, acuminate, base cuneate, glabrous; petioles 0.5-2 cm. Inflorescence of solitary (rarely paired), axillary flowers, peduncles 3-6(-16) cm; bracteoles c. 1 mm, elliptic, scarious, caducous; pedicels 13-21 mm; sepals very unequal, coriaceous, glabrous, margins scarious, outer 10-16 
<normalizedToken id="3BFF6CFAF208AF622784DBE23414A2A2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
6-7 mm, oblong-elliptic, mucronate to retuse, inner 16-23 
<normalizedToken id="3E0FBFEEA8C99CD158E1959F7B11D8F0" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7-8 mm, obovate, rounded; corolla 6.5-11 cm long, funnel-shaped, white with pink throat, glabrous, limb 4-5 cm diam., lobed with apiculate lobes. Capsules 2 
<normalizedToken id="6F958A8583726B366CEC2D0AEF11E920" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.5 cm, ovoid, rostrate, the mucro 3-5 mm, glabrous; seeds 11 
<normalizedToken id="648F5CF9F2D8A4A96CF191164E64FB0A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5 mm, black, glabrous but except for the pilose margins with hairs 3-4 mm long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
